name: Overwatch Blender Porn Style
description:
( ͡° ͜ʖ ͡°)

Note: The LORA name is "AbsurdlyGoodOW3DPornStyle", the example images use the development name.

V2:

  • Is a LORA again

  • Trained at 768x768, booru tag style

  • useful additional prompts: rim lighting, stylized 3D render, 3D, absurdres, sunny

  • Sometimes likes to generate multiple views/girls (might be tied to arhoangel prompt) or bad anatomy, put these in the negative prompt

  • Dataset consists of about 500 top quality Yeero and arhoangel renders and video frames (extracted one per animation via a script). Generally speaking solo renders were vertical, sex animations were horizontal.

  • still a bit finnicky sometimes but with these results i don't care, might further finetune it later

V2Beta:

Note: The V2Beta version is not as good as i initially thought. I'll try and get a proper V2 going but in the meantime i'll leave this version up for those who want to try it anyway.

  • it's a LoCon now, trained at 768x768

  • Much better at making 3D clothes and "coop gamemodes" now

  • suggested strength:0.8

  • best used with a character lora

  • rim lighting, stylized 3d render, 3d, overwatch, blender, arhoangel (or yeero) are heavily recommended prompts

  • Check the example images for pretty good prompts ( <lyco:LoCon2reps6000-000002:0.8> is indeed this LoCon, i renamed it a bit late)

  • Dataset is now about 1000 images

V1:

it's 2 AM here so i'll keep it short for now:

  • trigger word is overwatch 3d porn style

  • suggested strength: 1

  • blender, 3d are relevant extra prompts

  • trained on about 620 overwatch porn renders from a handful of top artists, lazily grabbed using grabber with: "[artist name] overwatch -animated"

  • some character LoRAs work best at around 0.8 strength, other at 0.5 (especially 2D anime girls)

  • rule of thumb: the more clothes your character wears, the less 3D it will look

  • defaults to an absolute fertility goddess body

  • also tends to turn blonde characters into Mercy

  • trained on nai, works pretty good on Anything V4.5, where my example images come from

  • check the example images for decent prompts

As usual with my stuff, lots of room for improvement but i like what it does already and should really just go to bed

  • Expanded the dataset to include a single frame from from every animation in addition to previous regular renders. This seems to make it a lot better for "coop gamemodes" ( ͡° ͜ʖ ͡°)

  • V2Beta is a Lycoris/LoCon now, looks much better in certain situations, MUCH better at making 3D clothes

  • made with updated training tools, better trained in general, although i still have to tweak some parameters
